HEADWORD: Lovable
<hw>Lov"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having qualities
that excite, or are fitted to excite, love; worthy of love.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Elaine the fair, Elaine the <qex>lovable</qex>,⟦br⟧
Elaine, the lily maid of Astolat.</q> <rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

